# Styling Standards

## Colors
- Use Tailwind's orange-500/600 for primary actions and accents
- Use slate-700/800 for dark backgrounds
- Use white/slate-200 for text
- Maintain high contrast for accessibility

## Container Widths
- Use max-w-[84rem] for main containers
- Apply consistent padding: px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8
- Center containers with mx-auto

## Typography
- Use font-medium for regular text
- Use font-semibold for headings and important text
- Follow Tailwind UI typography scale
- Maintain readable line heights

## Gradients
- Use bg-gradient-to-r for buttons: from-orange-500 to-orange-600
- Use hover:from-orange-600 hover:to-orange-700 for button hover states
- Use bg-gradient-to-br for page backgrounds
- Maintain consistent gradient directions within sections

## Spacing
- Account for fixed navbar with pt-24
- Use consistent gap-8 for major sections
- Use space-y-6 for stacked elements
- Maintain breathing room between components

## Interactive Elements
- Use transition-all duration-300 for smooth animations
- Add hover:-translate-y-0.5 for subtle button lift
- Use ring-1 ring-white/5 for subtle borders
- Add backdrop-blur-sm for translucent overlays

## Responsive Design
- Use grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 for two-column layouts
- Ensure mobile-first approach
- Maintain consistent breakpoints (sm, md, lg)
